<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3170] XmlNodePrinter does not handle attribute namespaces correctly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3170</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following script fails, because XmlNodePrinter ignores the attribute namespace. The output of writer.toString() is &amp;lt;root &lt;/p&gt;
{www.foo.bar}
&lt;p&gt;type=&quot;foo&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;def attributeWithNamespaceInput = &quot;&amp;lt;root ns1:type=\&quot;foo\&quot; xmlns:ns1=\&quot;www.foo.bar\&quot;/&amp;gt;\n&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
def root = new XmlParser().parseText(attributeWithNamespaceInput)&lt;br/&gt;
def writer = new StringWriter()&lt;br/&gt;
new XmlNodePrinter(new PrintWriter(writer)).print(root)&lt;br/&gt;
assert writer.toString() == attributeWithNamespaceInput&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I attached a fix for XmlNodePrinter and updated the corresponding test class.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
